---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base
  title="About — Josh Andrews · Dorian Insights"
  description="Josh Andrews has spent two decades guiding leaders from unreliable, complicated analytics to answers they trust. Principal, Dorian Insights."
>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- HERO                                                         -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<header class="hero-about" id="top">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="hero-about-grid">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
        <h1>Josh Andrews</h1>
        <p class="title">Principal · Dorian Insights</p>
        <p class="lede">For two decades I've worked with leaders who felt buried by their own data — inside Fortune 500 organizations and at Tier 1 consulting firms — and helped them come out the other side with something simpler: clear answers they trust. Dorian Insights is how I do that work for you today.</p>
        <div class="cta-row">
          <a class="btn-primary" href="/#contact">Schedule a call <span>→</span></a>
          <a class="btn-secondary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/joshuaroyandrews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn ↗</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-photo reveal">
        <img src="/josh-andrews-web.jpeg" alt="Portrait of Josh Andrews, principal at Dorian Insights" loading="lazy">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- BACKGROUND                                                   -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="background">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Background</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>A guide <span class="quiet">who's walked this road.</span></h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="essay reveal">
        <p>Chances are I've seen a version of your problem before. Two decades in technology consulting — executing engagements inside multiple Fortune 500 organizations while handling all aspects of a modern data &amp; analytics practice at a Tier 1 consulting firm — means I've sat with a lot of leadership teams staring at numbers they didn't trust. The connective tissue across all of it: deep, hands-on technical work — modeling, pipelines, cloud warehouses, dbt — paired with the kind of direct executive communication that is usually walled off in larger consulting engagements.</p>
        <p>Dorian Insights is the practice around this work today: a senior-principal consultancy focused on data and analytics, business strategy, and the technology architecture that supports them. Most engagements involve direct platform work — across cloud data warehouses (e.g. Snowflake, BigQuery), dbt, and the broader modern data stack — always in service of a strategic question that started with your leadership team.</p>
        <p>Current focus areas include building and operating cloud data platforms; team and process design; integration of LLMs and AI into analytical workflows; and full-stack analysis from raw data through executive presentation. In every case, the aim is the same: your team, empowered with answers it trusts.</p>
      </div>

      <aside class="principal-card reveal">
        <div class="label">At a glance</div>
        <h3>Quick facts</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>20+ years in technology &amp; data consulting</li>
          <li>Multiple Fortune 500 engagements delivered</li>
          <li>Tier 1 consulting firm leadership background</li>
          <li>Cloud data warehouses (e.g. Snowflake, BigQuery) &amp; dbt</li>
          <li>SQL · Python · BI &amp; visualization</li>
        </ul>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- CAPABILITIES                                                 -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="capabilities">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <div class="section-marker">Capabilities</div>
      <div class="section-title">
        <h2>What that experience <span class="quiet">does for you.</span></h2>
        <p class="deck">Three pillars built up over two decades, used in some combination on most engagements — all in service of one thing: making your data and your decisions simpler.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="capabilities-grid reveal-stagger">
      <article class="capability">
        <span class="label">Consulting &amp; leadership</span>
        <h3>Senior delivery experience</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Large data &amp; analytics team leadership at Tier 1 consulting firms</li>
          <li>Execution and leadership inside multiple Fortune 500 clients</li>
          <li>Direct C-suite reporting and executive stakeholder management</li>
          <li>Major focus on business delivery alongside technical execution</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="capability">
        <span class="label">Technical expertise</span>
        <h3>Deep, hands-on platform work</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Cloud data warehouse architecture (e.g. Snowflake, BigQuery)</li>
          <li>Full-stack: modeling, pipelines, SQL, Python, dbt, BI &amp; viz</li>
          <li>Performance tuning, cost optimization, query plan analysis</li>
          <li>Current, practical integration of LLMs and AI into data work</li>
        </ul>
      </article>

      <article class="capability">
        <span class="label">Business &amp; financial acumen</span>
        <h3>Practical commercial sense</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>P&amp;L, ARR/MRR, gross &amp; net margin, utilization management</li>
          <li>Technology &amp; vendor contract negotiation, legal risk management</li>
          <li>Budget development, resource planning, staffing decisions</li>
          <li>Change management and metrics deployment across the org</li>
        </ul>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- =========================================================== -->
<!-- CONNECT                                                      -->
<!-- =========================================================== -->
<section id="connect" class="contact">
  <div class="container">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">Schedule a Call</span>
    <h2 class="reveal">Take the first step <span class="quiet">toward simpler data and easier decisions.</span></h2>
    <p class="lede reveal">The most useful first conversations are short, frank, and unguarded. Schedule a 30-minute call, drop a message through the form, or reach out by email or LinkedIn directly.</p>

    <!-- Google Calendar Appointment Scheduling button -->
    <div class="contact-booking reveal">
      <link href="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/scheduling-button-script.css" rel="stylesheet">
      <script is:inline src="https://calendar.google.com/calendar/scheduling-button-script.js" async></script>
      <script is:inline>
      (function() {
        var target = document.currentScript;
        window.addEventListener('load', function() {
          calendar.schedulingButton.load({
            url: 'https://calendar.google.com/calendar/appointments/schedules/AcZssZ2yZAt4o1tI0kNiuIGW5iHlMNpJpkZ7GZTIgVB6OPQAb4NPMPqy3JndE92pA-ckX_7vWvsflC_8?gv=true',
            color: '#1B1464',
            label: 'Schedule a call',
            target: target,
          });
        });
      })();
      </script>
    </div>

    <a class="contact-email reveal" href="/#contact">
      Or send a message <span class="arrow">→</span>
    </a>

    <div class="reveal">
      <a class="contact-secondary" href="mailto:hello@dorianinsights.com">
        Or email hello@dorianinsights.com <span class="arrow">↗</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="reveal">
      <a class="contact-secondary" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/joshuaroyandrews/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">
        Or connect on LinkedIn <span class="arrow">↗</span>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</Base>
